body.description: Product Introduction --ARESGAME AGK850 power supply is a high quality power supply that offers great value to gamers and system builders. Designed with stability and durability in mind, the AGK series is the perfect choice to power your gaming systems. Features ---Stable Output: offers your system more reliable and stable output voltages, providing more consistent power delivery ---High-Efficiency: 80 plus Gold certified, with 90% efficiency or higher under typical loads ---Fully Modular: Maximize airflow in the chassis and improve overall efficiency and thermal dissipation performance ---Ultra Quiet 140mm Fan: with intelligent fan speed control, quiet and durable ---Excellent Heat Dissipation: Honeycomb ventilation design combines with the fan function for better heat dissipation ---Charming Outlook: The SECC black coating casing, black bushing cables and connectors, and black fan help to bring a high-tech appearance to your system ---High-end VGA card support with modern PCI-E 6+2pin connector ---Convenient Cable Design: Long cable length at least 600mm supports high-end case and meets user’s needs of perfect cable management ---Magic Cable Tie: Help to keep your computer environment tidy and minimize space usage ---Full Protection: including OVP/UVP/OPP/SCP/OCP Specification --Model: ARESGAME AGK850 --Modular: Fully Modular --Watt: 850W --Type: Desktop ATX PSU --80 Plus: Gold Certified --VAC Input: 100V-240V --Fan's Size: 140mm/4.72inch --Product Dimensions:5.9x6.3x3.3inch Package Included 1 x 850W Power Supply 1 x AC Power Cord 7 x Modular Cables 1 x User Manual 1 x Quick Installation Guide 1 x Tester 4 x Hook and Loop Fasteners 4 x Screws 8 x Cable Ties

reviews.reviewText: I purchased this power supply unit for my grand children when I built their gaming PC. This 850 Watt is almost a clone of my Gold rated, fully modular PSU in my PC. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great RMA Process
reviews.reviewText: Overall PSU works well. First unit became faulty within a year. After some back and forth with the support team I shared the windows failure logs to show the failures were unexpected shutdowns due to power faults and not driver errors and they promptly sent out a new unit. New unit is working great and if I don't follow up then you can assume it has continued to perform well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 20, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars 13 months and then dead. Warrantied replacement arrived DOA. Company now non responsive.
reviews.reviewText: When I initially purchased this PSU, I was pleased as punch. It was a good fit for my personal build that fit my budget and the 10 year warranty was a good selling point until...13 months later, the PSU dies. I start the warranty process and was sent a AGT1000 PSU as a replacement since they were out of stock of the AGK850 PSUs at the time. Their initial response and handling of a warranty exchange was both prompt and professional. However, after the AGT1000 PSU arrived DOA, I proceeded to make the video the company requires showing it being non-functional, uploaded it, and sent several emails to the warranty / support email they provide to be completely ignored.The PC this PSU is intended for is my only PC. I homeschool my Autistic daughter with it and have not been able to do any schooling with her in 2 weeks since it is all online and I am unable to teach from phone screen. This has been very detrimental to her academic learning process as well as to her mental health because of the loss of structure and consistency she needs with her disability. This has been also included in my correspondence to Ares Games with no reaction from them.I would highly recommend not doing business with this company simply due to their own business practices in regards to their customers. Absolutely horrible follow through on their part.If they actually follow through, I will amend this review with that information. As of this moment though, I am disappointed in Ares Games and frustrated with their handling of this warranty issue.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 26, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Better quality than I expected!
reviews.reviewText: Expected a Chinese special in a plain box with crap instructions. PS came well packaged in a good looking box. Inside the box I found the PS to be well padded foam molded to the PS shape. (Good thing too, judging by the smashed box corner, the USPS wasnt gentle with it). All the cables and accessories came neatly in an impressive nylon velcro closure bag. The cables were neatly tied and well labeled. Mounting screws, zip ties, and Velcro cable management wraps were also included. They even threw in a PS test jumper molex connector.I'm pleasantly suprised by the unit and the company that made it so far! Definitely exceeded my expectations.

reviews.reviewTitle: Lose cable not psu gave me heart attack
reviews.reviewText: Thank you so much for the pamphlets. They greatly improved the installation process as I removed my old psu without memorizing which components were connected and to what. I must not have plugged in the 24 pin connector because when I turned the pc on it would restart every 3 seconds but after only pressing down on the 24 pin connector, everything was perfect. Noise is not unbearable as most of my pcs noise usually comes from fans or the random rattling of unknown parts. I was over powering a 450W 6 year old psu so it was way past the time to upgrade. Lastly, thank you for making the psu affordable. $100 for 850W? Good deal! Sucks for people without graphics cards though!
Bought it because I thought it was the power supply that was broke. This worked great but it wasn't what was broken.
Came out of the box dead, changed all the cables and it didn't work. Waste of time and money, amazon should remove the 80+gold rating its far from the truth. Buyers beware.

reviews.reviewTitle: Dans l'espoir que mon PC démarrera un jour...
reviews.reviewText: Bonjour. Alimentation modulaire achetée en vue de remplacer mon ancienne alimentation au standard 220v de la France. ARESGAME est une marque inconnue dans l'hexagone et j'ai donc fait confiance aux commentaires. Dès réception, j'ai pu constater qu'il s'agit de matériel de qualité. Le packaging est au top et l'ensemble est plutôt sympa au niveau esthétique. Par contre, depuis l'échange dans mon boîtier, seuls les ventilateurs fonctionnement ! Je suis plutôt calé en informatique, mais là, c'est le néant !!! L'alimentation fonctionne avec le testeur inclus, mais pas lorsque la fiche 24 pins est connectée à ma carte mère... Ma config : carte mère B550 Aorus Élite V2, processeur Ryzen 5 5600 X, 12 Go de DDR 4 Corsair, ventirad Alseye et carte graphique MSI GTX 1080 TI Trifan. 750w suffisaient pour faire tourner cette configuration en France... Pourquoi pas au Québec ??? Si quelqu'un a une solution, je suis preneur. Bien cordialement. Christophe

Honestly this power supply is a super good purchase for someone who doesn't care about "name brands". Serves the exact purchase as the big boys and works just as well. Super quiet. Easy install. Nothing but good things to say about it.
